summary: Honestly Loki is a really underrated character and as much as I r e a l l y want more female superhero films, holy shit do I...
body:
Honestly Loki is a really underrated character and as much as I r e a l l y want more female superhero films, holy shit do I want a Loki film.

He’s really just… a piece of shit. Not a huge piece of shit, but big enough that if you stepped in him you’d strongly consider ever wearing those boots again.

‘God of Mischief’ undersells so much of what he’s capable of, whereas ‘God of Chaos’ is more like it, because chaos holds so much more gravitas than mischief.

I want a Loki film directed by Taika Waititi, where Loki is in all his gold and green decadent glory, eating grapes like the Hedonist-bot in Futurama.

I want a Loki film where he realises that order is just chaos people have become accustomed to.

I want a Loki film where he’s goddamn Iago, completely silent when there’s more than one other person with him but the minute it’s 1-on-1, he puts everything he’s observed into action and shows us he’s master manipulator.

I want a Loki who genuinely doesn’t care whose weaknesses and triggers get exposed and exploited, and who will use psychologically harmful methods to achieve his aims because ‘it’s for the greater good! you heroes love that right! hahahaha ¯\_(ツ)_/¯’

I want a Loki film where when the title is first introduced it initially says ‘THOR’ in red and lightning blue and then fades to ‘LOKI’ in green and gold and your queer ass knows it’s in for two hours of 150% levels of d r a m a t i q u è.

summary: The gift of a wolf || open starter
title: The gift of a wolf || open starter
body:
The honey colored wolf paced the cage it was in, limping slightly as he did so, obviously wounded and scared. The cage was carried in by several strong men and placed on the floor in a dimly lit area of the room.

“I do hope with the gift of this young wolf, you will see your way to keeping the peaceful accords between our peoples. Think on it, of course. Either way, the wolf is yours to keep. He has no family or pack that will come looking for him. He will be able to change back into his human form in a few hours if you wish him to do so.” The men left and the wolf stopped pacing and lay down in the cage, blue eyes watching the shadows near him in a wary manner.

body:
Marvel Headcanon 2

Shuri and Peter meet Baby Groot and fall in love instantly

I mean obviously, he’s the cutest thing to ever exist and now they spend every waking moment with him

They like to help him climb up places and learn to use Earth objects

Shuri is constantly tracking and observing the fluctuations in his voice and the actions that follow so that maybe maybe she can learn the Groot language and she and him and Peter can have conversations that *most* everyone else can’t understand

Quill is highkey against that idea so obviously Rocket starts helping Shuri learn it just to piss him off

There’s a strict rule that Baby Groot stays inside the compound bc the world is a big place and he could get lost so easily

But Shuri and Peter wanna take him everywhere bc he’s a baby and he just gets so excited about everything and they love watching him be happy

“Where do you two think you’re going?”

“Oh we’re just going to the movies Mr. Stark, no need to worry”

“You can’t take Groot with you.”

“What? We don’t have Groot with us!!! What are you even talking about????”

“Peter I can see him in your pocket, why is he even in there?”

“Well you found him so easily every time we hid him in Shuris purse…”

But anyways, the best day of Peter and Shuris life is when Quill tells them Groot will dance to any song, any time, anywhere

This just spurs on their love of singing as loudly and obnoxiously as possible as they walk through the compound, they try out a ton of songs every day, Baby Groot happily skipping and dancing right behind them

So Steve has been keeping up with internet memes, because he’s not really sure what an adult in this time is supposed to know versus what adults of this time don’t really care about, so he just keeps researching anything trending on the internet just to keep up with it all

He notices that a lot of the songs Shuri and Peter sing are ones that are commonly trending in internet videos

When the video of the boy singing it in the car circulates the internet again, Shuri and Peter sing nothing but Unwritten by Natasha Bedingfield for a week straight, and while Baby Groot didn’t get tired of it once, everyone else collectively ban Peter and Shuri from singing it ever again

So one day Steve is clicking through twitter trying to catch up with whats going on in the world, there’s a video with a bunch of likes and retweets so he clicks on it, worrying about the possibility of it being referenced by someone in the future, but the moment the video starts playing he turns it off instantly, the song that had been playing in the background was atrociously annoying and he could barely handle the few seconds he had heard

Suddenly, he feels fear grip his heart, if this video had become this popular… surely not, maybe if he got to Stark soon enough and asked him to make sure this song was never played in the compound ever, he could stop the possibility of Peter and Shuri ever hearing it, and therefore save everyone in the compound from the torture of them serenading Baby Groot with it for a week straight

But as he stands up he realizes he’s too late

He slams his hands down in frustration, he was defeated before he could even try and now a week of suffering is on its way

He can hear their voices singing together in the distance, slowly getting louder and louder

“Baaaaaaby Groot, do do do do do do do do”
